Here are the determined details for the endpoint that uses App\Http\Controllers\UserController@update (PUT|PATCH):

- Full HTTP request path: /settings/account

- All HTTP methods acceptable: False

- DELETE: False

- PATCH: True

Explanation:
- The update method is registered under the settings prefix as part of an authenticated and verified user group:
  Route::prefix('settings')->group(function () {
      Route::match(['put', 'patch'], 'account', [UserController::class, 'update'])->name('users.update');
  });
- This means the endpoint path is /settings/account and only HTTP methods PUT and PATCH are handled by this route.
- HEAD, POST, GET, DELETE, OPTIONS, and TRACE are not supported by this route according to the code, so they are not acceptable for this endpoint. The HEAD handling for non-GET routes is not defined in this route.
